article.headline: St. Louis 58, Marquette 54
article.story: St. LOUIS (AP) -- Chris Sloan scored 13 points and Josh Fisher and Izik Ohanon hit key free throws down the stretch to lift Saint Louis University to a 58-54 Conference USA win over slumping Marquette Wednesday. The Golden Eagles, (13-9 4-7) who made the Final Four last year, are in jeopardy of missing the NCAA tournament after losing their fourth straight game. Marquette wasted a game high 26 points from guard Travis Diener. Steve Novak gave the Golden Eagles a 54-53 advantage with a 3-pointer with 44 seconds left in the contest. But Fisher gave Saint Louis (13-9 6-5) the lead back at 55-54 when he converted two free throws with 30 seconds left. Ohanan, who finished with 11 points, made three free throws with just under 16 seconds left to seal the win for Saint Louis.
